          <td valign="top" width="1" ><img src="/magic/gfx/trans.gif" width="18" height="2" vspace="0" hspace="0" border="0"></td>
          <td  valign="top"><!-- #BeginEditable "Body" --> 
            <BR><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><font class="h1font"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="9cb6d7c984c9b1846fc3d3415e4ddb43" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<tr height="10"><td width="98%" bgcolor="#333333" height="10"><img src="/magic/gfx/trans.gif" width="6" height="2" vspace="0" hspace="0" border="0"></td><td valign="bottom" align="right"><img src="/magic/gfx/hrz/tk.gif" width="103" height="10" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0"></td>
</tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td valign="top" align="right">
<img src="/magic/gfx/hrz/bk.gif" width="92" height="24" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0"></td>
</tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Onslaught<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/magic/gfx/star2.gif" width="20" height="20" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magic/gfx/star2.gif" width="20" height="20" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magic/gfx/star2.gif" width="20" height="20" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magic/gfx/star2.gif" width="20" height="20" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(3.75)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/magic/main/mpage.php?member=4008'>Lyle "Pikachu87" Waldman</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magic/main/mpage.php?member=4008&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> September 1, 2002</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> Of course, we must all face the time when we say goodbye to our children their first day of school, work, college, camp, and so on, but on a much more cardboard-related note, we must also say goodbye to our favourite cards when a new block comes.  That is, of course, if we want to keep our decks legal for Type 2 (Standard).  As Onslaught is right around the bend (releasing sometime in early October), I am going to cover all the stuff that will leave us when Invasion and its little brothers, Planeshift and Apocalypse, say goodbye.<br />
<br />
Invasion was not a huge set.  It was not one of those awesome sets that everyone cares about like the Mercadian or Urza blocks were.  Nevertheless, we still do lose some important and interesting cards.  For my first topic, let me cover my favourite hobby: Theme Decks.  In Invasion, we had the Kavu.  For all who don&#39;t know and have been sleeping for the last 3 years, the Kavu are primarily green and/or red creatures with the creature type &quot;Kavu&quot;.  They come in different sizes, different casting costs, and, this most notable in the ever-annoying Kavu Chameleon, different colors.  They range from the 6/6 (with Kicker, correct me if I&#39;m wrong) Kavu Titan to the smaller 2/2 and 3/3 Kavus.  Gone with the Kavu is the most utterly stupid ability there is: Protection from Kavu.  Protection is only for colors, not for creatures.  The official rule here would state &quot;This creature cannot be blocked by creatures of Kavu type, cannot be targeted by Kavu spells or abilities, and all damage done to this creature from Kavu sources is reduced to 0&quot;.  Imagine, for a moment, if we replaced the word &quot;Kavu&quot; with, say, Elemental:&quot;This creature is immune to all Elemental sources of damage, cannot be blocked by Elemental creatures, and all Elemental damage done to this card is reduced to 0&quot;.  Logically, this would satate that any damage done through any of the natural or scientific elements to this card is reduced to 0, thus giving the creature unblockability and invincibility, as all matter is made up of 1 of those 2.  Anyway, enough ranting about Protection from Kavu.  Some interesting Kavu are the Kavu Titan which is (correct me if I&#39;m wrong) a 3/3 with a Kicker which makes it a 6/6 trampler.  There is also the Kavu Chameleon which is a 4/4 who can change its color for G.<br />
<br />
The next thing we lose is the Kicker ability.  Certain cards have this ability to make them stronger.  For instance, Desolation Angel, the remake of Selenia, Dark Angel (same character, new look) has a kicker of WW and acts as an Armageddon if you pay the kicker.  Then there&#39;s the all-so-annoying Llanowar Elite.  This card is the only natural 1/1 trampler in all of Magic.  If you pay its kicker of 8 generic mana it becomes a 6/6 trampler.  9 mana for a 6/6 trample...I&#39;d rather have a Scaled Wurm.  Then again, Scaled Wurm is not trample.<br />
<br />
Anyway, the next topic is Planeshift&#39;s Gating.  Gating is the ability of a select few gold (multicolored) creatureswhich allow you to return a creature of one of their colors to your hand when they come into play.  Remember that they are already in play and they are (unless you use Thran Lens or Darkest Hour), their own color.  hus, if they or any of your other creatres have a comes-into-play ability, you can use it over again.  This is especially good with Pandemonium.  Gone are the days of the 7/7 trample Shivan Wurm for 5 mana.<br />
<br />
And last, but not least, one of my favourite cards leaves with Invasion.  Coalition Victory is the first tournament-legal card I can remember which says &quot;If you fit a certain condition, you win the game&quot;.  I like cards that do this.  They&#39;re fun.<br />
<br />
Anyway, I&#39;ve had fun writing this article and I hope you&#39;ve taken a lot out of it.  Until next time, Chao! <br></font><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/magic/articles/articles.php?id=4031&view=1&PHPSESSID=9cb6d7c984c9b1846fc3d3415e4ddb43'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/magic/articles/articles.php?PHPSESSID=9cb6d7c984c9b1846fc3d3415e4ddb43'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/magic/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=9cb6d7c984c9b1846fc3d3415e4ddb43'> become a registered member</a></font><BR></td></tr></table>
